testcase.name: CREATE TABLE `t1` ( `id` int unsigned NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `name` varchar(191) NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`id`) ) ENGINE InnoDB, CHARSET utf8mb4, COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
CREATE TABLE `t2` ( `id` bigint unsigned NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `t1_id` int unsigned NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`id`) ) ENGINE InnoDB, CHARSET utf8mb4, COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
CREATE TABLE `t3` ( `id` bigint unsigned NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `name` varchar(191) NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`id`) ) ENGINE InnoDB, CHARSET utf8mb4, COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
select group_concat(t3.name SEPARATOR ', ') as "Group Name" from t1 join t2 on t1.id = t2.t1_id left join t3 on t1.id = t3.id group by t1.id;
